 MIAMI GARDENS, FLORIDA – MARCH 23: Alexander Zverev of Germany congratulates David Ferrer of Spain after his win during the Miami Open Tennis on March 23, 2019 in Miami Gardens, Florida.   Julian Finney/Getty Images/AFP  Ferrer, ranked 155th in the world, is on a farewell tour in 2019, having said he’ll play a limited number of ATP tournaments. He received a wild card into the Miami draw and advanced to a third-round meeting with American Frances Tiafoe, a 7-6 (8/6), 7-6 (7/5) winner over Miomir Kecmanovic. Zverev, seeded second behind Serbian Novak Djokovic, coughed up a dozen double faults in the two-hour, 22-minute contest. The defeat follows the German’s third-round exit at the Indian Wells Masters last week.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .